In this task, I optimized a machine learning model using Optuna for efficient hyperparameter tuning. Instead of manually testing different parameter combinations, I used an automated search process with cross-validation to find the best-performing model. The optimization was based on classification accuracy, and all trials were logged for reproducibility. After completing the search, I selected the best parameter combination and evaluated it on the dataset. This task helped me understand how hyperparameter tuning improves model performance while reducing unnecessary computation.